  "text": "Transactional Programming: It is straightforward to write transactional programs with ASF. A transaction is mapped to a speculative region whose memory accesses are done with LOCK MOVs between a SPECULATE and a COMMIT. However, it is more likely that average programmers use high-level TM language constructs and rely on TM compilers to optimize the use of LOCK MOVs to run transactions efficiently with limited ASF hardware resources. In [CITATION_1] , a TM compiler is developed to generate the ASF code from C/C++ programs written with high-level TM language constructs. It optimizes the speculative memory footprints of the ASF code by analyzing speculative regions, identifying memory accesses that do not require speculative accesses such as certain stack accesses, and not using LOCK MOVs for them.",
